---
description: Procedural shader art coding rules for GLSL, Shadertoy, SDF, heightfield, material, and atmospheric shaders
globs:
  - "**/*.frag"
  - "**/*.glsl"
  - "shaders/**"
alwaysApply: false
---

Read `prompts/universal-system-prompt.md` and relevant references in `skills/codex/shader-art-coding/references/`.

Use Shadertoy-compatible GLSL by default. Keep `mainImage(out vec4 fragColor, in vec2 fragCoord)`.

Use `iDebugMode`:

- `0`: final render
- `1`: scalar field / SDF contours
- `2`: normals
- `3`: material IDs
- `4`: step count / depth
- `5`: masks / density
- `6`: lighting terms

Use formal mathematical helper names for reusable code. Run `npm run check` after substantial shader changes.
